Story: "Simple Regex Test"
Purpose: "Test basic regex functionality"
Context: "Pattern matching demonstration"

State:
  text = "hello123world"

Steps:

1. Test if text contains digits
   Effect: has_digits = text MATCHES "\\d+"
   Because: Check for digit pattern
   Then: has_digits will be true or false depending on regex library

2. Extract digits from text
   Effect: digits = EXTRACT "\\d+" FROM text
   Because: Extract numeric sequence
   Then: digits will contain "123" if regex works

3. Display results
   Effect: result_msg = "Text contains: " + text
   Because: Build output message
   
4. Show result
   Effect: PRINT result_msg
   Because: Display the result

End: Return "Regex test completed"
     Because: Demonstrated regex operators
